overview: The user initiated a project to develop a sleep questionnaire
  application, requiring a database for response storage, an admin dashboard for
  data access, and an authentication system. The assistant evaluated the
  existing codebase, clarified requirements for demographics and authentication
  complexity, and then developed a comprehensive plan. The implementation
  involved updating demographic fields, creating a Prisma model for
  questionnaire responses, building API endpoints for data submission,
  retrieval, and CSV export, and developing an admin dashboard. A key decision
  was to simplify the authentication system from custom session management to a
  more streamlined Next.js middleware approach, which effectively protected
  routes and managed user sessions with a simple password. After providing
  detailed database setup instructions, the assistant conducted thorough
  testing, confirming that all implemented features, including database
  interaction, API functionality, and authentication, were working as expected.
  The project concluded with atomic commits reflecting each logical change.
